From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: robert-brunson-fragile <siinspam@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 20:51:55 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 09/19] feat(api): realtime resumable session sync subscription

Add /api/sessions/{id}/subscribe: an SSE endpoint that emits a snapshot,
catch-up state, and replayable live run events for clients that drop
into an existing API session, then keeps them current with a push-based,
standards-resumable sync stream. Also expose lightweight live state on
session list and detail responses so clients can show active work
without N+1 calls.

- SessionSyncNotifier: per-session wakeup fanout. Every in-process
  event writer signals subscribers when it commits, so delivery does
  not wait on a poll timer. A 2s poll fallback remains for writers
  in other processes sharing state.db.
- hermes_state module-level session-event listener hook: the agent
  persists transcripts through its own SessionDB instance, so the
  notifier registers process-wide and wakes subscribers on any
  instance's session_events write (fired post-commit, never inside the
  write lock).
- Composite resume cursor v1:<event_cursor>:<run_id>:<run_seq> carried
  as the SSE id: on every frame. Reconnects resume via the standard
  Last-Event-ID header (EventSource works with zero client
  bookkeeping) or an explicit ?resume= param; after/cursor/run_after/
  after_seq params are also supported. Header beats query params
  because EventSource re-sends the original stale query string on
  auto-reconnect.
- Startup recovery appends a synthetic run.interrupted replay event
  (at last_seq + 1) for runs orphaned by a server restart, so resuming
  clients learn the run died instead of hanging; fresh snapshots show
  status=interrupted. run.status events surface status transitions
  that have no replayable event (e.g. /halt).
- ResponseStore writes serialized behind a lock (agent callbacks write
  from executor threads onto a check_same_thread=False connection).
- docs/api-session-sync.md documents the full protocol; capabilities
  advertise session_sync_resume.

Tests: tests/gateway/test_session_sync.py covers composite cursors,
Last-Event-ID reconnects, legacy params, multi-client fanout,
push-beats-poll latency, cross-thread/instance wakeups, restart
interruption visibility, and join-in-progress/run.switch;
TestSessionEventListeners covers the hermes_state hook.

Co-authored-by: Nako <280596805+nakoagent@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

